Place your @Irish beef strips{250%grams} in a #bowl{}. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment
after handling raw meat and its packaging.

Add the @soy sauce{1%sachet} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Leave aside to marinate.

Trim and quarter half the @cucumber{1/2}(trimmed and quartered) lengthways. Chop into small
pieces. Add to a bowl with the @yoghurt{75%grams} and season to taste with salt and pepper.

Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Trim the @carrot{1}(trimmed and coarsely grated) then coarsely grate (no need to peel).

Halve the @cherry tomatoes{125%grams}(halved).

Finely chop the @parsley{10%grams}(finely chopped) (stalks and all).

Zest the @lemon{1}(zested and cut into 4 wedges) and chop into 4 wedges.

To a #medium bowl{}, add the @couscous{100%grams}, lemon zest and @salt{1/4%tsp} (double
for 4p).

Pour @boiling water{200%ml}(about 200ml) into the bowl.

Give it a stir, cover with a #plate{} or #cling film{} and leave aside until ready to serve.

When cooked, stir the grated carrot through the couscous. Season to taste with salt and
pepper.

While the couscous cooks, whisk together @oil{4%tbsp} (double for 4p) with the juice of
half the lemon wedges in a large bowl.

Add the @dried chilli flakes{1%sachet} (use less if you don't like spice), garlic and
chopped parsley.

Stir to combine and season to taste with salt and pepper.

> TIP: Use a blender if you'd like a smoother consistency.

Place a #large pan{} over high heat with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}.

Once hot, remove the beef strips from the marinade and fry until browned, ~{5-7%minutes},
shifting as they colour.

When ~{1%minute} cooking time remains, add any marinating juices from the bowl to the pan.

> IMPORTANT: Meat is safe to eat when the outside is browned.

Divide the couscous between #bowls{}.

Top with the cherry tomatoes and cooling cucumber.

Finish with the beef strips and a drizzle of the chimichurri sauce.

Serve with remaining lemon wedges for squeezing over.